&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Intro 
    &lt;div id=&#34;intro&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While browsing &lt;strong&gt;YouTube&lt;/strong&gt; I stumbled upon a video showing off a neat little tool called &lt;strong&gt;Zoxide&lt;/strong&gt;. It&amp;rsquo;s touted to be a smarter &lt;code&gt;cd&lt;/code&gt; command, inspired by &lt;code&gt;z&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;autojump&lt;/code&gt;. It remembers which directories you use most frequently, so you can &amp;ldquo;jump&amp;rdquo; to them in just a few keystrokes. &lt;strong&gt;Zoxide&lt;/strong&gt; works on all major shells.&lt;/p&gt;


    
    &lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
